{
  "texts": [
    "At the same time, we need to introduce the concept of \"operation,\" which refers to a simple function of one or more variables.",
    "When multiple operations and variables are combined, more complex functions can be described, and forward propagation calculates the output z produced by the input x.",
    "The difference between the target value ẑ and z is represented by the loss function L(ẑ, z).",
    "To produce the optimal solution, the backpropagation algorithm is executed to update the parameters.",
    "By recursively using the chain rule, the gradient can be calculated directly."
  ]
}